en_60137_0	A proposal submitted by the Ministry of Water Supply & Drainage Board to establish a bottled water factory has been turned down by the Attorney General.
en_60137_1	The Ministry had forwarded this proposal with the aim of providing portable water to those in the North Central Province, who have been hard hit by kidney disease.
en_60137_2	According to the Secretary Ministry Amarananda Abeygunawardhana plans were underway to have the water bottled through a company affiliated to the Ministry.
en_60137_3	However due to legal constraints the proposal had been turned down by the Attorney General.
